      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Be unto me a father and a priest.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—The title “father” is here ecclesiastical, like “papa,” “pope,” &c, and this title was given to spiritual directors, as we find in several other passages in the Bible (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2Kings 2:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2Kings 5:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2Kings 6:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 22:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", &c.). Micah knew enough of the law to be aware of the extreme irregularity of his conduct in making one of his own sons his priest.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Ten shekels of silver.—Thus the grandson of Moses became priest of an idolatrous worship at a salary of 25s. a year!",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Ten shekels of silver.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Thus the grandson of Moses became priest of an idolatrous worship at a salary of 25s. a year!",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "By the year.—Literally, by days. (Comp. Leviticus 25:29.)",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "By the year.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Literally, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "by days. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(Comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Leviticus 25:29",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".)",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "A suit of apparel.—The Vulgate renders these words “a double robe.” It seems to mean either “an order of garments” or “the value of garments,” i.e., “your clothes.”",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "A suit of apparel.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
