  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Micah made this proposal to the Levite: \"Dwell with me, and become my father and priest; I will give thee ten shekels of silver yearly, and fitting out with clothes and maintenance.\" אב, father, is an honourable title give to a priest as a paternal friend and spiritual adviser, and is also used with reference to prophets in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 6:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 13:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and applied to Joseph in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 45:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ליּמים, for the days, sc., for which a person was engaged, i.e., for the year (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 27:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 25:29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). \"And the Levite went,\" i.e., went to Micah's house. This meaning is evident from the context. The repetition of the subject, \"the Levite,\" precludes our connecting it with the following verb ויּואל. - In ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 17:11-13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the result is summed up. The Levite resolved (see at ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 1:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") to dwell with Micah, who treated him as one of his sons, and entrusted him with the priesthood at his house of God. And Micah rejoiced that he had got a Levite as priest, and said, \"Now I know that Jehovah will prosper me.\" This belief, or, to speak more correctly, superstition, for which Micah was very speedily to atone, proves that at that time the tribe of Levi held the position assigned it in the law of Moses; that is to say, that it was regarded as the tribe elected by God for the performance of divine worship. ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
]